I think both correlate and they combine for what was shown in those tables and in your chart. In every category more schooling led to more liberalism and lower pay generally led to more liberalism (aside from HS or less arguably) so the statement seems to still be accurate. No? “Lower income + higher education level is the sweet spot for DSA candidates” what am I missing ?

